His aim was clearly to win May's European elections which they did to put the fear of god into the Tories. That happened and the Tories got rid of May, elected Johnson as their leader, pursued a much clearer and more direct route to Brexit, brought back a new deal when people said it couldn't happen (me included) and have won a very comfortable majority. Farage has got exactly what he wanted. Plus in the meantime he made plenty of money and caused plenty of disruption in the European parliament.
